  "texts": [
    "t (x t |y 0:t), t = 0, 1,.",
    ", T, is typically achieved via a particle filter, which we consider in the next section.",
    "The bootstrap particle filter (see e.g.",
    "Gordon et al., 1993) consists of a sequence of weighted resampling steps, whereby upon receipt of y t, N state particles x 1:N t-1 = {x 1 t-1,.",
    ", x N t-1 } are propagated forward via some proposal density, appropriately weighted and resampled with replacement."
  ]
}